<topic id="tpc_tables">
    <title>Tables</title>
    <body>
        <p>There are several ways to create a table using <abbreviated-form keyref="ditaot"/>. In general the simpletable is quite
            easy to use:</p>
        <p>
            <simpletable frame="all" relcolwidth="1.0* 1.89*" id="simpletable_urb_zb1_mx">
                <sthead>
                    <stentry>Column 1</stentry>
                    <stentry>Column 2</stentry>
                </sthead>
                <strow>
                    <stentry>Monday</stentry>
                    <stentry>Get up early.</stentry>
                </strow>
                <strow>
                    <stentry>Tuesday</stentry>
                    <stentry>Get up late.</stentry>
                </strow>
                <strow>
                    <stentry>Wednesday</stentry>
                    <stentry>Stay in bed.</stentry>
                </strow>
            </simpletable>
        </p>
        <p>However, the CALS Table is much more flexible and gives you more options.</p>
        <p>
            <table frame="all" rowsep="1" colsep="1" id="table_d5l_fc1_mx">
                <title>CALS Table Title</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                    <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="2.0*"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>Column 1</entry>
                            <entry>Column 2</entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>Thursday</entry>
                            <entry>Visit Uncle Joe</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>Friday</entry>
                            <entry>Get back on track.</entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>Saturday</entry>
                            <entry>Gain faith.</entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </p>
        <p>Please note that the CALS table has a title. This title can be included in the table
            references in the backmatter of the document. Check it out.</p>
        <p>In case you are using an WYSIWYG<fn>WYSIWYG: <u>W</u>hat <u>Y</u>ou <u>S</u>ee <u>I</u>s <u>W</u>hat <u>Y</u>ou <u>G</u>et.</fn> editor there is no reason to not use the CALS
            table.</p>
        <p>Please also mind that both tables are rendered differently. Actually the {met√¶ffekt}
            DITA-OT customization does currently not pay particular attention to using simple
            table.</p>
    </body>
